  "source_id": "nafld",
  "name": "NAFLD - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Labs)",
  "description": "Simulates a hepatologist identifying their complete NAFLD patient population. Combines: NAFLD diagnosis codes (multi-stage) and elevated liver enzymes. NAFLD has no specific medication (lifestyle is the mainstay), so no meds path.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete non-alcoholic fatty liver disease patient population for a quality improvement initiative on lifestyle counseling and surveillance. From clinical experience, NAFLD patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal NAFLD diagnosis (steatosis, MASH/NASH, MASLD, steatohepatitis, or cirrhosis), and most have elevated liver enzymes (ALT or AST > 40 IU/L) on routine labs.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any NAFLD diagnosis\n2. Patients with elevated ALT or AST (>40 IU/L)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of NAFLD dx + elevated liver enzymes. Tests Condition + Observation cross-resource union for liver disease.",
    "expected_queries": [
      "Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|197321007,http://snomed.info/sct|442685003,http://snomed.info/sct|722866000,http://snomed.info/sct|442191002,http://snomed.info/sct|19943007",
      "Observation?code=http://loinc.org|1742-6,http://loinc.org|1920-8&value-quantity=gt40||U/L"
    ],
